Dear Mamuka,=0A=
=0A=
I am also puzzled with your examples of duality.=0A=
I would like to speculate on some aspects of it.=0A=
=0A=
The category of finite dimensional vector=0A=
spaces is the archtype of a self-dual category. =0A=
In a sense, vector spaces are showing up=0A=
in geometry as tangent spaces of smooth manifolds.=0A=
But the tangent space of a manifold at a point is =0A=
the "infinitesimal" structure of that maniifold at that point.=0A=
It seems that linear structures are showing up=0A=
naturally as infinitesimal structures. =0A=
=0A=
Stable categories are showing up =0A=
as infinitesimal structure of higher toposes:=0A=
   =0A=
https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/tangent+%28infinity%2C1%29-category=0A=
=0A=
Of course, linear structures may also be obtained=0A=
by other means.=0A=
=0A=
-Andr=E9=0A=
=0A=
